==Description==

The [[Image:SheetMetal_AddCutout.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_AddCutout|SheetMetal AddCutout]] command does...

==Usage==

# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:SheetMetal_AddCutout.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_AddCutout|Extruded Cutout]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|SheetMetal → [[Image:SheetMetal_AddCutout.svg|16px]] Extruded Cutout}} option from the menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|E}} then {{KEY|C}}.

==Notes==

==Properties==

See also: [[Property_editor|Property editor]].

A SheetMetal ExtrudedCutout object is derived from a [[Part_Feature|Part Feature]] object or, if it is inside a [[PartDesign_Body|PartDesign Body]], from a [[PartDesign_Feature|PartDesign Feature]] object, and inherits all its properties. It also has the following additional properties:

===Data===

{{Properties_Title|Base}}

* {{PropertyData|Proxy|PythonObject}}: 

{{Properties_Title|Extruded Cutout}}

* {{PropertyData|CutSide|Enumeration}}: Default is {{value|Inside}}. Side of the cut.
* {{PropertyData|CutType|Enumeration}}: Default is {{value|Through everything both sides}}. Cut type.
* {{PropertyData|ExtrusionLength1|Length|hidden}}: Default is {{value|500.0 mm}}. Length of the extrusion direction 1.
* {{PropertyData|ExtrusionLength2|Length|hidden}}: Default is {{value|500.0 mm}}. Length of the extrusion direction 2.
* {{PropertyData|SelectedFace|LinkSub}}: The selecteds object and face.
* {{PropertyData|Sketch|Link}}: The sketch for the cut.

{{Properties_Title|Extruded Cutout Improvements}}

* {{PropertyData|ImproveCut|Bool}}: Default is {{value|False}}. Improve cut geometry if it enters the cutting zone. Only select true if the cut needs fix, 'cause it can be slow.
* {{PropertyData|ImproveLevel|IntegerConstraint|hidden}}: Default is {{value|4}}. Level of cut improvement quality. More than 10 can take a very long time.
* {{PropertyData|Refine|Bool}}: Default is {{value|False}}. Refine the geometry.

